description: From Middle English impellen, borrowed from Latin impell≈ç.

verbs.description: impel (third-person singular simple present impels, present participle impelling, simple past and past participle impelled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To urge a person; to press on; to incite to action or motion via intrinsic motivation.
examples: Antonym: (to compel or drive extrinsically) propel

entries.meaning: (transitive) To drive forward; to propel an object, to provide an impetus for motion or action.
